detaileddescription.para: So, say we have a model like: model { species{boundary = false} species{boundary = true} species{boundary = false} species{boundary = true} species{boundary = true} ... } Using 0 based indexing, if index = 0, we'd get the compartment name for species 1, index = 1 yields compartment name for species 3, index = 2 yields compartment name for species 4, and so forth.

detaileddescription.para: In SBML assignment rules does not have to appear in the correct order. That is you could have an assignment rule A = B, and a rule B = C. Now the result would differ, if the first rule is evaluated before the second. Thus the rules will be reordered such that this will be taken care of.
